On this week’s episode of Health Theory, join me as I reveal the daily habits that help me perform at an elite level. 

If you have followed me for any amount of time, you have likely heard me say action cures all. Since starting Healthy Theory, I have interviewed over 90 specialists and experts about everything from brain cognition, to gut microbiome, to reverse aging. Information is meant to be put into action, so today I am sharing with you what my daily routine consists of at the moment. This episode is Health Theory In Action.

To watch the entire episode on your favorite platform, click the link in bio.

node.text:
I am not a born entrepreneur. What I am is relentless. At first I was relentless about making money which burned me out. Now, I am relentless about chasing FULFILLMENT, and it’s this pursuit, the dogged determination of finding and satiating my need to live a life worth living, that drives me every day. In shifting my focus I have been able to build massively successful companies, avoid burn out, and truly live! But it took me YEARS, no fucking joke, YEARS to get here. 

If you are looking to find fulfillment and get real results in your business I want to invite you to join my Business Decision Making Workshop. This is a 4-week intensive for anyone with a 6-figure+ business looking to take things to the next level and think differently about how they overcome their problems. This is the distillation of all the years I spent building businesses. It is the same rubric I use every day as I build Impact Theory. 

If you want to join, click the link in bio. It is time to make it happen!

node.text:
The people that surround you will shape you. So be very careful who you draw into your circle. 

When I met @lisabilyeu I did not plan to get married. But there was something about her. I wasn’t just attracted to her, she made me feel better about myself and pushed me to reach for more. So even though everyone thought that we were making a huge mistake - because we were so young (she was only 22 and I was just 26), and we’d only been together for 8 or 9 months when I proposed - we both believed this could work. Even back then we knew it would take work, we knew we wanted to improve, and we believed that together we’d become a lot more than we would by ourselves. So we ignored all of the nay sayers and committed ourselves to the relationship. And I can say now beyond a shadow of a doubt that that was the single best decision I’ve ever made in my life. We have continued to shape and improve each other and I can honestly say I would not be the same person without her. So, if you’ve found the one, don’t be afraid to defy the odds. Just be prepared to put in the work, push each other, and grow together. 

And Baby, to you I say, Happy Anniversary!!! Thank you for pushing me and making my life something I love more than I ever could have imagined. I Love you beyond all reason and measure.

Oooooooh! Big announcement time! I've been DYING to talk about this for a while! My insanely talented wife @lisabilyeu has secured a book deal with @simonandschuster via @atriabooks!!! I am beside myself with pride and excitement. Her journey from unfulfilled house wife to high-level entrepreneur has been one of the most incredible transformations I've ever witnessed - and that is the subject of the book. If you've ever felt you were meant for more, this book is going to be the road map you need to turn your dreams into a reality.  

Many of you may already know her, but by way of brief recap: Lisa was raised in a traditional Greek household. It was super loving, but she grew up being told that the end goal for her was to be a good housewife. That's an amazing life if that's what you want, but she didn’t. 

As my business career became more and more demanding she found herself spending all of her time facilitating my work. I used to refer to her as the CEO of Bilyeu Industries because outside of business, she took care of every aspect of our lives. 

Then we launched Quest. Now, I wish I could say that I was smart enough to realize that she was a legendary entrepreneur wasting away inside the house, but the truth is that I just needed some help. And, as an ULTRA supportive wife, who wanted to see me win, she agreed. But once she got in the mix she really started to come alive. It was such a striking transformation as she shifted into a totally new gear (definitely safe to call that gear Beast Mode). It was the mental equivalent to watching someone add 50 lbs of muscle to their physique - awe-inspiring to say the least. 

Through the book, Lisa is going to walk you through her insane transformation, including how to manage all of the brutal emotional ups and downs of that kind of radical change. From the avalanche of self-doubt to how to beef up your skillset, she covers it all.

Best of all, you can join her as of right now. CLICK LINK IN BIO and sign up for updates, with glimpses into her journey and the book, BTS of Women Of Impact, special challenges and giveaways, and so much more!! I hope you’ll join her. Be legendary, my friends!

📸 @peter_hurley
